; Tests that a SPIR-V binary whose instruction WordCount is below the minimum
; required for that instruction is rejected with InvalidWordCount rather than
; silently causing integer underflow when resizing variable-length operand arrays.
;
; In the .spt text format the word count is written explicitly as the first
; token on each line.  OpDecorate requires at least 3 words (header, target,
; decoration), so WordCount=1 on the last line is malformed.
;
; RUN: not llvm-spirv %s -to-binary -o %t.spv 2>&1 | FileCheck %s
;
; CHECK: InvalidWordCount:

119734787 65536 0 6 0
2 Capability Kernel
3 MemoryModel 1 2
1 Decorate 5 RelaxedPrecision
